Step-by-step install bash linux ubuntu on windows

1. Your PC must be running a 64-bit version of Windows 10 Anniversary Update build 14393 or later
2. In order to run Bash on Windows, you will need to manually:
   - Turn-on Developer Mode (Open Settings -> Update and Security -> For developers)
   - From Start, search for "Turn Windows features on or off" (type 'turn')
   - Cheklist -> Windows Subsystem for Linux (beta)
3. Open a PowerShell prompt as administrator and run:
   - Paste ( Enable-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online -FeatureName Microsoft-Windows-Subsystem-Linux )
   - Open a command prompt 
   - # bash
   - Create a UNIX user

Referensi :
-> https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/commandline/wsl/install_guide

